	details = <
		["en"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::en]>
			purpose = <"To provide a single, rapid assessment of nutritional status in elderly patients in outpatient clinics, hospitals, and nursing homes.">
			use = <"Use to evaluate the MNA-SF score on geriatric patients ≥ 65 years.
Maximum MNA-SF score possible is 14; 
≥12 points = normal (no need for further assessment) 
8 - 11 points = at risk of malnutrition 
<8 = malnourished
A score <12 requires further assessment and possible intervention.
If greater specificity is desired consider 10 points or below as possible malnutrition.">
			keywords = <"MNA-SF", "nutrition", "elderly">
			misuse = <"">
			copyright = <"© Cambio Healthcare Systems">
		>
		["sv"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::sv]>
			purpose = <"För att utvärdera den totala poängen för Mini Nutritional Assessment">
			use = <"Används på geriatriska patienter i åldern 65 eller över.
The 6 items include:
 - food intake in the last 3 months (score 0-2), 
 - weight loss in the last 3 months (score 0-3), 
 - mobility (0-2), 
 - psychological stress/acute diseas in the last 3 months (0-2), 
 - neuropsychological problems (0-2) and 
 - body mass index (or calf circumference, 0-3)
Higher scores are indicative of better nutritional status. Maximum score possible is 14, and a score of ≥12 points = normal (no need for further assessment), score 8 - 11 = at risk of malnutrition and score <8 = malnourished. A score <12 requires further assessment and possible intervention.
If greater specificity is desired consider 10 points or below as possible malnutrition.">
			keywords = <"MNA-SF", "näring", "undernäring">
			misuse = <"">
			copyright = <"© Cambio Healthcare Systems">
		>
	>
